column5: Those damn voices do it every time
Best thing to do is take the lead and put it out for discussion. Don't need to be admin to organize a GTG.
The standard rules apply so I'll say it... NO PICS NO GTG! HH

Gerritt  Huh sure sums up what I put Earlier today and I sure love AutoCorrect. What I was trying to say is I was talking to squid On the cell phone when he was at the GTG I recognized some of the voices around the table and heard new ones I did not know. I had Pete say hi to everyone for me after we got off the phone. I felt like I was the phone a friend for him.
Now it makes sense lol
I guess I should make sure to wait to make my first post of the day. 4:52 bc (Before coffee) Was not at good choice. Next time it'll be 4:52ac Then everything might make some sense
Those who WERE there have the best pics, memory pics....
Yup, it was great listening to your stories Albert!
Julie and I will be there.
Shall be there.
Looks like 7 confirmed, anyone else?
I'm still in with my better half, see you all there!  Tony
Glad to hear it Tony.  I'm looking forward to seeing old friends and new friends.
Is every body dropping like flies .. Hope we have a good show as I will be there for sure
Good to hear Kelvin!
I most probably will be there as well.
I'm a definite no John.. not a good week here.
1 day!
Enjoy. I can't make it due to last minute business travel.  Edit: raising my double rye to you all while on my train ride back to home. I hope everyone has a great time and safe travels.
Looking forward to seeing some old and new faces tonight!!
Would have LOVED to get out but I'm running a fever. The last round of chemo kicked my butt. Here's to next time. Cheers folks!!
38.2 and you're supposed to hit Emerg Bigbuck!!!  Have fun tonight folks.... got one here we're looking after ourselves!
So, how did it go????  Any pictures????
Went well, nice putting faces to those names.   lots if last minute cancels though.
So how many people actually showed up?
13 people or so showed.
Hope everyone had a blast !!!! I have been to several g2g and always had fun and met new people and freinds
We could do one in Toronto Great sports bar and food on Lawrrsnce ave east and warden called the loaded dog

The problem is we are all spread all over and depending on where the g2g is sometimes its hard for people to come from long distances. !!! Almost need a north,east,west,south g2g contrary to popular belief Toronto is not the center if the universe. !!! Lol....
Lol! Wherever it is ill try to be there
Maybe the next 1 can be just North of TO, say Vaughan to Newmarket. Making it into the inner city(Anything Lawrence or below is a major PITA for those not used to it. The traffic---yi, yi, yi!
It was nice to hear everyone again and the voices I did not know I guess in the way I was there Kinda only a friend style.
Huh?
I need the change count me in
That's awesome Kelvin, really looking forward to seeing you again!
25 brave men and women so far.......
Cant make this one  Maybe next time!

Doesn't fit the chemo schedule at this point.. but it might work if she decides the week following that she wants to be home in her apartment for the weekend. I've got the date marked.. we'll see what happens.
I am in too ... I even gave it my fav color in Outlook - greeeeeeen
bump
Just keeping it visible
Just getting it back on page 1
Just moving it TTT until we can get it pinned in a few days
Bump...
are we getting any more people to come out .. what is the count now
Think we are probably 30 plus Kelvin.
What's this date again...
Dec 7, 7pm

that is great I can't wait to see some friends again it been a long battle and I need a break for sure yesterday would have been her 58th birthday and we went to the cemetery and changed the wreaths and today marks 10 months since she passed..

Trust me it will get eaiser not saying this in a mean way but you will move foward and no you will never forget move but not forget you will never get that piece of your heart back I feel for you my friend I really do  Peter

Was just informed my wife will be away that weekend. She's heading down to Grove City on a Christmas shopping spree with the girls.  So...I'm at home with the kids that weekend. We were originally going to drop the kids off at my sister in laws then head to Bronte, but my sister in law is joining my wife.  If I can find someone to watch the kids I'll be there guys, otherwise I'm pooched.
Leave em! LOL
My daughter could babysit.
Only 8 days left!
If there will be anyone around at about 9pm I will drop by for a pop.
Just confirming for next week.
I'll be there for as long as every one else is....
Still good to go
Because the girls there thought we were cute all in our yellow jackets.
I should be able to get there.

I would be willing to drive the 3 hours if it was on a weekend or a Friday night. I would end up making a weekend out of it by fishing the area too.  I met back then "EH" for the first time. You know, there are some things you regret in life... and that wasn't one of them. Can't forget the "Jester". Good times it was.  Cheers, Ron...
Bump
The Firehall is almost my local so assuming I'm around, I should be up for this - Saturday night is "Oakville Idol" - always good for a laugh
Sounds like fun, but I have a ton of work travel between now and the end of November. December is wide open, but I'm pretty much pooched till then.
One more bump to the top looks like a December Fri or Sat is the way to go...
A December date should be doable.
Dang - this is in the GTA!  Mr. Borger, MJL and Spiel are in, count me in too....
Wow...Been a while! I'm in with the Mrs. for whatever date (Preferrably not Tuesdays)
OK, I am booking Friday, December 7th, 6.00pm. Head count seems to be 15-20.  Peter, considering this is your thread are you OK with that?
Sounds good to me!
Its in my neck of the woods. Depending on how I feel, I will try to stop in for a wing or two.
If I get home early enough to make the drive I will.

Bring on the wings...Maybe some fish n' chips  I'll try to duck out of work early...Possibly to hit up a river on the way  No manager in their right mind would think someone with "violent diarrhea" is lying
Hmmm. Maybe we should chat and possibly car pool part of the way. I am just easy of London and considering to join the party.
Awesome, I'll be there with Joanne.
Yer sick.LOL

OK boys and girls, couldn't get reservation for 6 so it is 7.00pm Friday December 7th at The Firehall corner of Lakeshore and Bronte Road Oakville. They don't take reservations before 7pm Friday nights.  Please could you PM me and confirm numbers. I have reserved for 20 but by the response I can see it getting bigger. So don't be shy please let me know ASAP.  J...
Gonna bump this back to the top until we can get it pinned
It can get pinned in 17 days John.  Dang, I wish I could go.
We wish so too bud. You could form La Belle Provence contingent and hire a coach..........
sorry reno mode Im good with it i will see you all there   thanks john  Peter
No worries Peter, thanks for planting the seed!
I'm in
So how about a get together at the Fire Hall in Bronte sometime before Christmas Im open to dates just sniffing the wind right  now. Havent seen one there in quite some time  What do you think  Peter
Sounds like a good idea, we're way overdue.
Sounds good tome, just expect me to be down at the river for a while.
Pick a day when they have 2for1 Wing night for us retired folks.
Lotsa good memories from the Firehall gtg's Pete, wish I was lots closer and I'd be there for sure.
Great idea Peter. keep sniffin' should I inquire as to when 2 4 1 wings are on?
OK Tuesday is 2 4 1 wing night...  http://www.thefirehall.ca/  23rd Oct, 13th Nov work for me any thoughts Peter...
I can probably make it work
im good with what the clan wants lets git er done

How about I book a table for November 13th.......spouse and significant others welcome? Let me know numbers guys and gals. I will be there with the lovely Barbara come rain, shine or that white stuff!  Thanks for planting the seed Peter!
I'm sure I can swing it and because I'm without a vehicle I'll get the lovely Miss Julie to accompany me.
Sounds like a plan...I will make sure that I don't have a vehicle either...
OK I guess I jumped the gun. They don't take reservations on 2 4 1 wing night, first come first seated. Any thoughts guys and gals?
An opp to meet some more OFCer's???  Me and the Mrs. are in.
yep, cause your missing soooooooo much  :whistling:
I'd be interested but couldn't do it on a Tuesday.  Thurs, Fri or Sat would work for me.  Also may I suggest something in December?
I'm also a weekend only person can't take time off work for it.

Nothing magical about Tuesdays. To me the most important thing is to give as many as possible the opportunity to GTG. Lets give this a few days to see who else is in and we can go from there. Maybe a Friday night?
Pending date and time... you never know. Not a long haul from Jen's but it was the last time we did the firehall all the way from home!
I did the same Wayne drive up from Chatham met new friends talked with some I already knew and drove home it was a great night.
I'd be interested in a G2G. If it's in Oakville and on a weekend, I may be tempted to hit up a nearby river or two before and after the swill
A pre G2G G2G? I like it!
I am in anytime( Obviously)!!
We did a nice one in London I would be in for again.
I wonder why...
